                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I read the posts about folks quitting playing their enchanter after the OOW fiasco and I wanted to bring up the subject, since I feel somewhat the same about my bard as many seem to feel about their chanter.
<br />

<br />
Let me introduce myself first.  I played an enchanter till mid 50 lvl, about the time velious became popular, when I got so disgusted with the no mezz rule in kael on raids, decided I didn't wanna play a "buff bot" for raids, so I started a bard.  Now my bard is time flagged, had a total blast getting there with my guild, I have enjoyed raiding immensely, but  had limited time to play in 2004, so have done very little in GoD.  What I have seen of GoD makes me think that bards are of limited usefulness there.
<br />

<br />
The info I have seen on OOW makes me pretty sure that bards are one of the weakest of the weak sister classes, perhaps even worse than the enchanter.  A couple of things I read about bards replacing chanters in groups these days made me squirm a bit.
<br />

<br />
First, I don't think bards can ever do any crowd control as well as chanters.  True, bard mezz in GoD is pretty reliable, and resists are mostly irrelevant IF the mob is agroed on the bard.  BUT!  bard mezz is SLOW!  I dunno how many times I have seen a pull go wrong and three mobs in camp, all mezzed by me, and no one but me alive in the group.  (I was NOT pulling btw, hehe!  Shoulda been i guess)  Bard mezz has no agro, so the bard cant run around the camp while recasting cause the add is eating the cleric instead.
<br />

<br />
Second, I think that while the DPS of enchanters has been severely nerfed in the most inept way possible, I think that enchanters are still more useful as a DPS class than bards are in a group.  Bards do SAD melee damage,  when they can melee.  And bard damage compared to warrior damage at lvl 70 is significantly less than bard damage compared to warrior damage at lvl 65.  Add in the focus caps, it just gets worse.
<br />

<br />
We do have one advantage over enchanters tho.  The order in which we get our songs is just not a issue with bards, unlike enchanters.  ALL the bard songs are crap.
<br />

<br />
Perhaps the game has just finally run its course.  Perhaps you can't just go on indefinitely adding content to the game, increasing the level limits and abilities of players.  I dunno.  But I don't have the time to reroll my bard as another class and lvl up.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
