                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Bards slow is not as good as an enchanters but having a mob preslowed before it enters the camp saves more mana then slowing the mob a little bit more after the mob gets below 80 percent.
<br />

<br />
Harmony plus bard slow is almost as easy to stick as tash and slow,  and a bard gets a lot less aggro from slowing then an enchanter will.
<br />

<br />
A bard adds more dps to a group because he can overhaste the melee by 30 percent and increase the dps of casters.   As it is how often does a caster not have kei on themselves then you add the bard mana song for a lot more mana regen.
<br />

<br />
A bard can do CC on the run,  when an enchanter a silk class gets a resist he has to stand still and try and cast a spell through a beating, while a bard a plate class just kites and mob and mez it while running.
<br />

<br />
In OOW where people are always looking out for named mobs, having a bard over an enchanter means the group has a good puller that can CC and slow and haste and mana regen and overhaste and best of all save a lot of clearing by just pulling the names or PH's.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
