                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I played a bard for a bit. After a while I decided, I will never play a bard again. I really disliked the class. They are very difficult to play and require a lot of concentration and dexterity that I dont have. I look at the number of bards on our server compared to other classes and despite being overpowered there are not a lot of them. Probably for many of the same reasons I have. I have always thought of bard power as compensation for the difficulty of the class. I have had far more problems with bad druids than bards (nothing against druids, just druids that don't know how to play their class.)
<br />

<br />
We get in these debates about who is worse off, but, if you listen carefully, you will see that every class has problems. OOW did not discriminate against classes, it nurfed everyone. We all lost class abilities. 
<br />

<br />
I cant understand why we insist on having contests about whos been nurfed the most. If enchanters, bards, rangers, bezerkers, shamans, wizards, druids, monks etc would get together with one unified voice then perhaps SOE would take the class issues more seriously.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
