                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I would say that bards while not being "ridiculously overpowered" are more or less just balanced.  I'd say they are still useful for a lot of reasons
<br />

<br />
-Some mobs in oow run so fast I'd think the only way to pull them without say casting at max distance and running back to the group, which would limited the radius around the group that you can pull, is with a bard.
<br />

<br />
-Bards I would definitely say are better at handling a single add that hits very hard/fast much better than enchanters due to their ability to cast while running.  I've never seen a 3 mob or more than 2 mob in any numbers train.  In otherwords, all trains I've seen sort of favor bards, since if they get a resist, they have more options than taking 7k+ damage trying to mez is, and then if mind over matter isn't up, maybe say 9k or 14 k or whatever.  I'm judging this by riftseekers.  Being that I was in a high level guild, I don't consider low end of the expansion content to be a reason to play my char, but I haven't seen a situation where you'd need to have an add in the camp in any zone except say if you're a newbie that's not pulling to a safe spot in the first zone.
<br />

<br />
-Bards have more ac, so if they do decide to/have to tank, they have a slightly better chance of it being a plate class.
<br />

<br />
Frankly at this point, I would imagine people would feel safer with bards doing any needed crowd control/pulling than enchanters.  But at the same time, I am definitely not saying that bards are overpowered in any sense, since their swarm kiting ability has been nerfed, and even then I never really saw that as so great, since it really  involves a fair amount of risk to me, if you experience a lag spike or go linkdead, or just mess up a bit, you die, losing what from my experience watching bards was 20 minutes of work at most.  I would honestly say compared with classes like warriors clerics and so on, bards are a balanced class and can sufficiently do the job that is presented in oow.  I would also say I consider this a good thing.  Maybe I've missed something, maybe bard mezmerizes resist a lot at the higher levels, but I doubt it.
<br />

<br />
I could never play one though, due to way too much button pressing.  I could understand anyone getting tired of the class in that respect.  =P</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
