		<td width="150" align="left" valign="top" class="row2"><a name="80045"></a><span class="name"><span class="usercolor">Yakk</span></span></td>
                <td class="row2" width="100%" height="28" valign="top"><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                        <tr>
                                <td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td><a href="viewtopic.php?p=80045#80045"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails">Posted: Mon Oct 18, 2004 9:40 am<span class="gen">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp;Post subject: </span></td>
                                <td align="right" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><a href="posting.php?mode=quote&amp;p=80045"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/lang_english/icon_quote.gif" alt="Reply with quote" title="Reply with quote" border="0" /></a>    </td></tr></table></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I still ain't gonna rush out and buy OOW though. I still don't think the reward is in line with the time investment in playing to lvl 70. And honestly, in a raid these days, I for sure wouldn't be recruiting more than one bard, two at most. Bein the fourth bard on a raid is about as useful as bein the fourth enchanter, possibly less, despite what someone said earlier about bard dps vs enchanter dps.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Resists.  Every bard is a group of people with max resists.
<br />

<br />
Overhaste.  While sub optimal, a bard in a group of 5 damage dealers turns into a damage dealer himself with the overhaste/DD focus songs.
<br />

<br />
Pulling.  You will want at least 1 bard pulling.
<br />

<br />
AoE mana.  You will want at least 1 bard singing aoe mana.  Sometimes you want more than 1 to get good coverage.
<br />

<br />
AoE resists.  Depending on layout, you want 1 or more bards singing aoe resists.  Often you want more than one to get good coverage.
<br />

<br />
Crowd control.  The tricky part of raid CC is usually lockdown.  Bards beat enchanters at lockdown.  In the case of a long-duration mez, on low resistance mobs bards can do it afk (and, with /melody coming, should be able to do high resistance mobs reliably).
<br />

<br />
About the only reason you want more enchanters over bards is aoe mez, slightly higher burst DPS, charm and more MGBs if the raid wipes alot.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
