                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I love my bard, and I feel quite usefull.  That asside, fade is the only thing keeping us from being pointless.
<br />

<br />
  The DPS a bard adds to a group even with overhaste/focus is much lower than another DPS class, in a group of 5 dps classes we barely add more damage maybe 10% more than another dps.  IMO it shouldn't be this way.  The resists we add mean very little or nothing in the end game.  Our mana regen and resist debuffs are nice.  And that pretty much sums up our so called force multiplier abilities.
<br />

<br />
  But, we can pull/CC nice due to casting mez on the run and fade.  Which makes the class pretty damn sweet at the level I play at (non raiding).</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
