                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">The resists we add mean very little or nothing in the end game. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Bard resist song is the only thing that means anything.  I can't cap my resists in anything now with just resist buffs.  But its trivial to cap any 3 resists with one ae song.  Also its trivial to cap all 5 resists if a bard is in group.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">The DPS a bard adds to a group even with overhaste/focus is much lower than another DPS class</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Bards and any melee class can outdamage enchanters in groups now.  Sustained nuking damage is horrid in oow in comparison to anyone who whacks things.  Bard burst dps is indeed very poor and even chanters can handily beat them in that area.
<br />

<br />
Non-raiding bards who don't have the minimal amount of raid gear required are indeed not badly out of tune.  Fixing percussion mods (hi, lets smoke a bunch of crack and make an item that adds +270% when we're afraid to add even +25% to caster nukes) and removing the haste (why exactly do bards also need to be able to cap haste?) from songblade/sombrenotes would be solid changes that wouldn't affect non-raiders.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />-<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=648415" target="_blank" class="postlink">Londo Mollari</a>
<br />
 Tholuxe Paells</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
